UIA maintains close relations with various lawyers' organisations across the world, such as the American Bar Association (ABA) and its various sections, the Arab Lawyers' Union (ALU), the Council of Bars and Law Societies of Europe (CCBE), the International Bar Association Conference (CIB), the Inter-American Bar Association (IABA-FIA), the International Bar Association (IBA), the Inter-Pacific Bar Association (IPBA), the Law Association for Asia and the Pacific (LAWASIA), the Presidents of Law Associations in Asia (POLA), the Syracuse International Institute for Criminal Justice and Human Rights (SII), the Unión Iberoamericana de Colegios y Agrupaciones de Abogados (UIBA) and the International Criminal Court Bar Association (ICCBA).&#xd;
&#xd;
At the same time, it maintains regular collaboration with local or national Bar Associations, some of them being members of UIA. As part of this collaboration, UIA may prepare analytical documents, send letters, including to bar associations, sovereign governments,  or issue a statement jointly on professional issues and on issues of human rights.&#xd;
&#xd;
Likewise, UIA occasionally works with non-governmental human rights organisations.
